      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "What Is a Vector Database?"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "A vector database stores high-dimensional float vectors alongside metadata payloads and provides fast "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "bold"
              }
            ],
            "text": "approximate nearest-neighbour (ANN) search"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": ". Unlike a relational database, which filters rows by exact column values, a vector database finds the K vectors geometrically closest to a query vector \u2014 in microseconds, across millions of items."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "image",
        "attrs": {
          "src": "data:image/svg+xml;base64,",
          "alt": "Write path: text \u2192 embed \u2192 upsert into HNSW index + payload store. Query path: text \u2192 embed \u2192 ANN search \u2192 fetch payloads \u2192 ranked results.",
          "title": "Vector Database: Write and Query Paths"
        }
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Key Concepts"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "bulletList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ],
                    "text": "Collection"
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": ": a named set of vectors with a fixed dimensionality and distance metric. Equivalent to a table."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ],
                    "text": "Point / record"
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": ": one vector + an id + an optional JSON payload (text, metadata, timestamps)."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ],
                    "text": "HNSW index"
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": ": the graph structure that makes ANN search fast (O(log N) instead of O(N))."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ],
                    "text": "Payload filter"
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": ": restrict ANN search to vectors matching a metadata condition (e.g. "
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "code"
                      }
                    ],
                    "text": "user_id == \"alice\""
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": ") \u2014 no post-filter needed."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Getting Started with Qdrant"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Qdrant is the recommended vector database for Claude agent projects. It runs locally as a Docker container or via the Qdrant Cloud managed service. The Python client is "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ],
            "text": "qdrant-client"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "bash"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "# Start Qdrant locally\ndocker run -p 6333:6333 qdrant/qdrant\n\n# Install client\npip install qdrant-client voyageai\n"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "from qdrant_client import QdrantClient\nfrom qdrant_client.models import Distance, VectorParams, PointStruct\nimport voyageai\nimport uuid\n\n_QC = QdrantClient(url=\"http://localhost:6333\")\n_VC = voyageai.Client()\nCOLLECTION = \"agent_memory\"\nDIMS = 1024\n\n\ndef ensure_collection() -> None:\n    existing = {c.name for c in _QC.get_collections().collections}\n    if COLLECTION not in existing:\n        _QC.create_collection(\n            collection_name=COLLECTION,\n            vectors_config=VectorParams(size=DIMS, distance=Distance.COSINE),\n        )\n\n\ndef upsert_chunks(texts: list[str], payloads: list[dict]) -> None:\n    ensure_collection()\n    vecs = _VC.embed(texts, model=\"voyage-3\", input_type=\"document\").embeddings\n    points = [\n        PointStruct(\n            id=str(uuid.uuid4()),\n            vector=vec,\n            payload={\"text\": text, **payload},\n        )\n        for text, vec, payload in zip(texts, vecs, payloads)\n    ]\n    _QC.upsert(collection_name=COLLECTION, points=points)\n\n\ndef search(query: str, k: int = 5) -> list[dict]:\n    q_vec = _VC.embed([query], model=\"voyage-3\", input_type=\"query\").embeddings[0]\n    hits  = _QC.search(collection_name=COLLECTION, query_vector=q_vec, limit=k)\n    return [{\"text\": h.payload[\"text\"], \"score\": h.score, **h.payload} for h in hits]\n"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Payload Filters"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Payload filters combine ANN search with metadata conditions in a single round-trip. Qdrant evaluates the filter on a filtered HNSW subgraph \u2014 much faster than post-filtering a full top-K result."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "from qdrant_client.models import Filter, FieldCondition, MatchValue, Range\n\n\ndef search_filtered(\n    query: str,\n    user_id: str,\n    min_score: float = 0.65,\n    k: int = 5,\n) -> list[dict]:\n    q_vec = _VC.embed([query], model=\"voyage-3\", input_type=\"query\").embeddings[0]\n    filt  = Filter(\n        must=[\n            FieldCondition(key=\"user_id\", match=MatchValue(value=user_id)),\n        ]\n    )\n    hits = _QC.search(\n        collection_name=COLLECTION,\n        query_vector=q_vec,\n        query_filter=filt,\n        limit=k,\n        score_threshold=min_score,\n    )\n    return [{\"text\": h.payload[\"text\"], \"score\": h.score} for h in hits]\n\n\n# Numeric range filter: only retrieve memories from the past 7 days\nimport time\nweek_ago = time.time() - 7 * 86400\nfilt_recent = Filter(\n    must=[\n        FieldCondition(key=\"user_id\", match=MatchValue(value=\"alice\")),\n        FieldCondition(key=\"created_at\", range=Range(gte=week_ago)),\n    ]\n)\n"
          }
        ]
      },
