          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Monitoring Collection Health"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Track index health and vector count over time to detect drift (vectors accumulating faster than the index can absorb them) and to trigger re-indexing when optimiser settings change."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "def collection_stats(collection: str) -> dict:\n    info = _QC.get_collection(collection)\n    return {\n        \"vectors_total\":   info.vectors_count or 0,\n        \"vectors_indexed\": info.indexed_vectors_count or 0,\n        \"status\":          info.status,          # \"green\" | \"yellow\" | \"red\"\n        \"optimizer_status\":str(info.optimizer_status),\n    }\n\n\nstats = collection_stats(COLLECTION)\nprint(stats)\n# {\"vectors_total\": 12340, \"vectors_indexed\": 12340, \"status\": \"green\", ...}\n\n# If vectors_indexed < vectors_total by a large margin,\n# the HNSW optimiser is lagging \u2014 wait or force optimisation:\n_QC.update_collection(\n    collection_name=COLLECTION,\n    optimizer_config={\"indexing_threshold\": 0},  # force immediate indexing\n)\n"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "End-to-End Agent Memory with Qdrant"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Combining the upsert and search functions from above, here is a minimal agent turn that saves each user message as a memory and retrieves the top-3 relevant memories before generating a reply."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "import anthropic, time\n\n_AC = anthropic.Anthropic()\n\n\ndef agent_turn_with_memory(\n    conversation: list[dict],\n    user_text: str,\n    user_id: str,\n) -> str:\n    # 1. Retrieve relevant memories\n    memories = search_filtered(user_text, user_id=user_id, k=3)\n    mem_block = \"\"\n    if memories:\n        lines = [f\"- {m['text']} (score={m['score']:.2f})\" for m in memories]\n        mem_block = \"<memories>\\n\" + \"\\n\".join(lines) + \"\\n</memories>\"\n\n    system = \"You are a helpful assistant.\"\n    if mem_block:\n        system += f\"\\n\\nRelevant memories about the user:\\n{mem_block}\"\n\n    # 2. Generate reply\n    conversation.append({\"role\": \"user\", \"content\": user_text})\n    resp = _AC.messages.create(\n        model=\"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001\",\n        max_tokens=1024,\n        system=system,\n        messages=conversation,\n    )\n    reply = resp.content[0].text\n    conversation.append({\"role\": \"assistant\", \"content\": reply})\n\n    # 3. Store this turn as a memory\n    upsert_chunks(\n        texts=[user_text],\n        payloads=[{\"user_id\": user_id, \"created_at\": time.time(), \"role\": \"user\"}],\n    )\n    return reply\n"
          }
        ]
      },
